"title": "5800: blasphemy",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5800",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The profaning, desecration and taking in vain of the name of God, or the reviling of any of his works or deeds. It is strongly forbidden by God as dishonouring to his name.</p>\n<h2>Blasphemy strongly forbidden</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:7\">EXO 20:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:11\">DEU 5:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:28\">EXO 22:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:21\">LEV 18:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:12\">LEV 19:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:32\">LEV 22:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:30-Num15:31\">NUM 15:30–15:31</a></p>\n<h2>Blasphemy against God punished</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:10-Lev24:16\">LEV 24:10–24:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:23\">LEV 24:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:20-2Kgs19:37\">2KI 19:20–19:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:21-Isa37:38\">ISA 37:21–37:38</a></p>\n<h2>Blasphemy against the Holy Spirit is unpardonable</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:28-Mark3:30\">MRK 3:28–3:30</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:31-Matt12:32\">MAT 12:31–12:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:10\">LUK 12:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:29\">HEB 10:29</a></p>\n<h2>God blasphemed indirectly</h2>\n<h3>Rejecting his word and his servants blasphemes God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:16\">2CH 36:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:11\">PSA 107:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:24\">ISA 5:24</a></p>\n<h3>Defiling sacred things blasphemes God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:1-Lev22:2\">LEV 22:1–22:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:27-Ezek20:28\">EZK 20:27–20:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:26\">EZK 22:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:6-Mal1:13\">MAL 1:6–1:13</a></p>\n<h3>Despising the poor blasphemes God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:31\">PRO 14:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:7\">AMO 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:5-Jas2:7\">JAS 2:5–2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Speaking against his people blasphemes God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:8-Zeph2:11\">ZEP 2:8–2:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:4-Acts9:5\">ACT 9:4–9:5</a> <em>To persecute the church is to persecute Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:9\">ACT 26:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:13\">1TI 1:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:9\">REV 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>Slandering celestial beings blasphemes God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:10-2Pet2:12\">2PE 2:10–2:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:8-Jude1:10\">JUD 1:8–1:10</a></p>\n<h2>The sins of God's people may cause others to blaspheme</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:1\">1TI 6:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13-2Sam12:14\">2SA 12:13–12:14</a> <em>The phrase “you have made the enemies of the LORD show utter contempt” reflects a scribal tradition which avoided any reference to blasphemy. The underlying idea of blasphemy would have been obvious to the original readers</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:20-Ezek36:23\">EZK 36:20–36:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:24\">ROM 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:5\">ISA 52:5</a></p>\n<h3>God's enemies blaspheme him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:20\">PSA 139:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:10-Ps74:11\">PSA 74:10–74:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:18\">PSA 74:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:25\">DAN 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:36\">DAN 11:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:3\">1CO 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:4\">2TH 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:5\">REV 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:9\">REV 16:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:11\">REV 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:21\">REV 16:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3\">REV 17:3</a></p>\n<h2>False accusations of blasphemy</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ falsely accused of blasphemy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:6-Mark2:7\">MRK 2:6–2:7</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:3\">MAT 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:21\">LUK 5:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:65-Matt26:66\">MAT 26:65–26:66</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:63-Mark14:64\">MRK 14:63–14:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:33-John10:36\">JHN 10:33–10:36</a></p>\n<h3>God's servants falsely accused of blasphemy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:9-1Kgs21:13\">1KI 21:9–21:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:11-Acts6:14\">ACT 6:11–6:14</a></p>",
